                    "company": "Bonn University",
                    "description": "My responsibilities included both PhD research and project co-ordination work in the context of a large international project SIR-C/X-SAR. Goals of the project were to assess and quantify the potential of multi-frequency multi-polarisation radar systems for agricultural remote sensing applications and general land-use classification. \n\nMy main tasks were:\n- to plan and co-ordinate in-situ measurement campaigns carried out in southern Germany and in northern and southern Italy during the 1994 Shuttle missions, in conjunction with partner agronomy institutes in Milan and Bari\n- to process and analyse the multi-frequency polarimetric data sets in conjunction with in-situ data\n- to develop and test classification methodologies adapted to polarimetric data such as Maximum Polarimetric Contrast classification or hierarchical schemes that exploit inter-polarisation coherence and phase information as well as backscatter values.\n- to assess the potential of multi-parameter SAR systems in terms of crop classification results and in terms of the sensitivity of multi-frequency multi-polarisation radar signatures to crop status. \n- to prepare technical reports detailing the results for the German Space Agency (DARA now DLR).",
